 commit service (F-008): createCommitService -> validatePreConditions/commit/recordCommit/getSessionCommits/checkPipelineStatus/checkTestStatus/buildCommitMessage\n  32→\n  33→TRAPS:\n  34→- chat operations are serialized by session key; keep async queue semantics unchanged\n  35→- pipeline-control-service must delegate to script-runner instead of shell string concatenation\n  36→- pipeline-controller must use lock-manager for concurrency protection (F-004)\n  37→- runSingle must NOT acquire lock (independent execution, D5)\n  38→\n  39→DECISIONS:\n  40→- 2026-03-10 | f001-pipeline-service | expose logs/reset methods in pipeline-control-service to satisfy US3 reusable control surface\n  41→- 2026-03-12 | f003-plan-ingestion | add plan-ingestion-service for schema validation, version management, and plan registry\n  42→- 2026-03-12 | f004-pipeline-controller | new module for unified pipeline control with lock management (D4)\n  43→- 2026-03-13 | f005-status-logs | add status-aggregator, log-pager, telegram-pusher for pipeline status aggregation and log streaming\n  44→- 2026-03-15 | f008-commit-workflow | add git-service and commit-service for commit workflow with pre-commit validation, audit logging (AC-5.3)\n  45→- 2026-03-15 | f008-exception-handling | add try-catch blocks in commit() function around validatePreConditions, gitService.commit/amendCommit, recordCommit, logAuditEntry calls to prevent crashes and ensure errors logged to audit trail\n  46→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce34148f809f24153c3d03a7c01aa","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:13:55.011Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"369890c5-f9c3-423d-a68b-13950146918b","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3414b3b636ab847a3bb498f69da","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: security\n   3→PATH: src/security/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Security guard layer for permission tiers, param sanitization, and confirmation flow\n   5→\n   6→KEY_FILES:\n   7→- src/security/index.js -> module exports\n   8→- src/security/permission-guard.js -> role hierarchy and command authorization\n   9→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js -> parameter sanitization and dangerous pattern detection\n  10→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js -> confirmation flow for high-risk actions\n  11→- src/security/guard.js -> existing user authorization\n  12→- src/security/system-guard.js -> system exec authorization\n  13→\n  14→INTERFACES:\n  15→- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'\n  16→- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n  17→- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean\n  18→- sanitizeParam(input, options) -> { ok, value?, error? }\n  19→- validatePath(path, allowedRoots) -> { ok, resolved?, error? }\n  20→- detectDangerousPatterns(input) -> { safe, patterns }\n  21→- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }\n  22→- checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> { status, action?, params? }\n  23→- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }\n  24→- cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> void\n  25→- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>\n  26→- queryAuditLogs(filters) -> Promise<Object[]>\n  27→\n  28→ROLE_HIERARCHY:\n  29→- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n  30→- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n  31→- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n  32→\n  33→COMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n  34→- status, logs: viewer\n  35→- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry: operator\n  36→- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n  37→\n  38→HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS:\n  39→- stop, reset, force-unlock -> require confirmation (CONFIRM text)\n  40→- admin can skip confirmation with --force flag\n  41→\n  42→DANGEROUS_PATTERNS:\n  43→- path traversal (..)\n  44→- shell injection (backticks, $(), ${})\n  45→- command chains (||, &&, ;)\n  46→- home directory expansion (~)\n  47→- exec/eval flags\n  48→\n  49→AUDIT_LOG:\n  50→- format: JSON Lines (.jsonl)\n  51→- fields: timestamp, userId, role, action, params, result, reason, sessionId\n  52→- rotation: max 10MB per file, max 5 files\n  53→\n  54→TRAPS:\n  55→- unknown users default to 'operator' role\n  56→- permission denied is logged before returning error\n  57→- confirmation expires after 60 seconds\n  58→- audit log write failures are silent (non-blocking)\n  59→- param sanitizer rejects all dangerous patterns regardless of context\n  60→\n  61→DEPENDS_ON:\n  62→- src/config.js -> USER_PERMISSIONS, ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM, AUDIT_LOG_*\n  63→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3414b3b636ab847a3bb498f69da","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:13:55.012Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"1a8bb870-431c-446a-8210-97fe72f6eeda","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3414d636c427e15f7559456583b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: bot\n   3→PATH: src/bot/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler\n  11→- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()\n  12→- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()\n  13→- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup\n  14→- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation\n  15→- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting\n  16→- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation\n  17→- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers\n  18→\n  19→SUBDIRS:\n  20→- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch\n  21→- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations\n  22→\n  23→INTERFACES:\n  24→- Telegram Commands:\n  25→  - /start - Bot startup greeting\n  26→  - /help - Dynamic help text\n  27→  - /reset - Clear chat session\n  28→  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot\n  29→  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command\n  30→  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)\n  31→  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)\n  32→  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management\n  33→  - /status [--type=feature|bugfix] - Show aggregated pipeline status (alias: /s)\n  34→  - /logs [--lines=N] [--offset=N] [--type=feature|bugfix] [--file] - View pipeline logs with pagination (alias: /l)\n  35→  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline\n  36→  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n  37→  - /commit [--message=\"...\"] [--amend] [--force] - Commit code changes with pre-commit validation (alias: /c)\n  38→  - /commits [--count=N] - View session commit history (alias: /history)\n  39→\n  40→TRAPS:\n  41→- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n  42→- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files\n  43→- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n  44→- Registry stores normalized command names\n  45→- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param\n  46→- F-005: /status uses status-aggregator for aggregated status; /logs uses log-pager for pagination\n  47→- F-008: /commit requires pre-commit validation (pipeline status + test status); --amend/--force require admin + confirmation\n  48→\n  49→DECISIONS:\n  50→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands\n  51→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l\n  52→- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands\n  53→- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management\n  54→- 2026-03-13 | F-005-status-logs | Update /status and /logs to use status-aggregator and log-pager with pagination support\n  55→- 2026-03-15 | F-008-commit-commands | Add /commit and /commits commands with pre-commit validation, session tracking, and admin confirmation for --amend/--force\n  56→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3414d636c427e15f7559456583b","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:13:55.014Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
