{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313021412cb835a3606424ca7","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"id":"20260313021412cb835a3606424ca7","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce3419e14f3ef1ee2dda5f2871aa8","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Context Snapshot - F-009: General Command Executor\n\n## Section 1 - Feature Brief\n\n### Feature Description\n通用命令执行引擎，将 PrizmClaw 从纯 pipeline 控制工具升级为通用远程 CLI 助手。用户在 Telegram 中发送任意 shell 命令（如 ls、git status、npm run build 等），Bot 在电脑端执行并将 stdout/stderr 回传。\n\n核心能力：\n- 基于现有 ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC 与 ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES 配置扩展，支持可配置的命令白名单/黑名单安全策略\n- 命令执行有超时保护（SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS），超时后自动 SIGTERM → SIGKILL 并通知用户\n- 长输出自动截断至 Telegram 消息长度限制并支持 /more 分页查看剩余内容\n- 支持通过 /cd 命令切换工作目录且目录状态在用户会话内保持\n- 命令入口格式：直接发送文本即当作 shell 命令执行（当 ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true），或使用 /exec <cmd> 前缀显式调用\n- 需要与 F-006 的权限系统集成，高风险命令（rm -rf、sudo 等）需要二次确认\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n1. 用户发送 shell 命令，Bot 在电脑端执行并返回 stdout/stderr 结果\n2. 支持可配置的命令白名单/黑名单安全策略，黑名单命令直接拒绝并提示原因\n3. 命令执行有超时保护，超时后自动终止进程并向用户返回超时提示\n4. 长输出（超过 Telegram 4096 字符限制）自动截断并支持 /more 分页查看\n5. 支持通过 /cd 切换工作目录，目录状态在用户会话内保持\n6. 高风险命令（含 rm -rf、sudo、kill 等关键词）执行前需用户二次确认\n\n### Dependencies\n- F-001 - Project Infrastructure Setup (completed)\n- F-006 - Safety and Permission Guard (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Section 2 - Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── adapters/\n│   └── codebuddy.js\n├── bot/\n│   ├── telegram.js          # Main bot factory\n│   └── commands/\n│       ├── index.js         # Command router\n│       ├── parser.js        # Command parser\n│       ├── registry.js      # Command registry\n│       ├── validator.js     # Parameter validator\n│       ├── formatter.js     # Error formatter\n│       ├── help.js          # Help text generator\n│       └── handlers/        # Individual command handlers\n│           ├── pipeline.js\n│           ├── bugfix.js\n│           ├── planner.js\n│           ├── status.js\n│           ├── logs.js\n│           ├── stop.js\n│           ├── plan.js\n│           ├── audit.js\n│           ├── commit.js\n│           └── commits.js\n├── http/\n│   └── server.js\n├── pipeline-infra/\n│   ├── config-loader.js\n│   └── script-runner.js\n├── routes/\n│   └── api-routes.js\n├── security/\n│   ├── index.js\n│   ├── guard.js             # User authorization\n│   ├── permission-guard.js  # Role hierarchy & command auth\n│   ├── param-sanitizer.js   # Parameter sanitization\n│   ├── confirmation-manager.js  # Confirmation flow\n│   └── system-guard.js      # System exec authorization\n├── services/\n│   ├── chat-service.js\n│   ├── chat-queue.js\n│   ├── session-store.js     # Session state management\n│   ├── system-exec-service.js  # System command execution\n│   ├── audit-log-service.js    # Audit logging\n│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js\n│   └── ...\n├── utils/\n│   └── logger.js\n├── config.js\n└── index.js\n\ntests/\n├── fixtures/\n│   ├── plans/\n│   └── states/\n├── security/\n│   ├── permission-guard.test.js\n│   ├── param-sanitizer.test.js\n│   └── confirmation-manager.test.js\n├── services/\n│   └── audit-log-service.test.js\n├── bot/commands/\n│   └── ...\n└── integration/\n    └── ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 3 - Prizm Context\n\n### root.prizm (L0)\n```prizm\nDOC_LEVEL: L0\nPROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\nPROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\nADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\nPLATFORM: codebuddy\nLANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\nPACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\nENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\nDOC_STATUS: initialized\nASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n\nDEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n```\n\n### runtime.prizm (L1) - Key Extracts\n```prizm\nDOC_LEVEL: L1\nMODULE: runtime\nPATH: src/**\nDESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n\nKEY_FILES:\n- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n- src/security/permission-guard.js\n- src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n- src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n- src/services/session-store.js\n\nINTERFACES:\n- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, /audit, /commit, /commits, text message relay\n- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService\n\nTRAPS:\n- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n- high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock) require admin role and confirmation\n- permission check happens before command handler execution\n- param sanitizer blocks path traversal and shell injection patterns\n- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n```\n\n### security.prizm (L2)\n```prizm\nDOC_LEVEL: L2\nMODULE: security\nPATH: src/security/**\nDESCRIPTION: Security guard layer for permission tiers, param sanitization, and confirmation flow\n\nROLE_HIERARCHY:\n- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n\nCOMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n- status, logs: viewer\n- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry: operator\n- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n\nHIGH_RISK_COMMANDS:\n- stop, reset, force-unlock -> require confirmation (CONFIRM text)\n- admin can skip confirmation with --force flag\n\nDANGEROUS_PATTERNS:\n- path traversal (..)\n- shell injection (backticks, $(), ${})\n- command chains (||, &&, ;)\n- home directory expansion (~)\n- exec/eval flags\n\nAUDIT_LOG:\n- format: JSON Lines (.jsonl)\n- fields: timestamp, userId, role, action, params, result, reason, sessionId\n- rotation: max 10MB per file, max 5 files\n\nTRAPS:\n- unknown users default to 'operator' role\n- permission denied is logged before returning error\n- confirmation expires after 60 seconds\n- audit log write failures are silent (non-blocking)\n- param sanitizer rejects all dangerous patterns regardless of context\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 4 - Existing Source Files\n\n### src/config.js\n```javascript\nimport 'dotenv/config';\nimport { z } from 'zod';\nimport { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\nimport { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n\nconst schema = z.object({\n  TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  ENABLE_TELEGRAM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  ALLOWED_USER_IDS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  CODEBUDDY_BIN: z.string().min(1).default('codebuddy'),\n  CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG: z.string().default('-y'),\n  CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(15000),\n  TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  TELEGRAM_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(120000),\n  MAX_PROMPT_CHARS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8000),\n  MAX_HISTORY_TURNS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n  WEB_HOST: z.string().default('127.0.0.1'),\n  WEB_PORT: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8787),\n  ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n  ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\n  LOG_LEVEL: z.enum(['fatal', 'error', 'warn', 'info', 'debug', 'trace', 'silent']).default('info'),\n  // F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n  USER_PERMISSIONS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  AUDIT_LOG_DIR: z.string().optional().default('logs'),\n  AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n  AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(5)\n});\n\n// ... parsing functions ...\n\nexport const config = Object.freeze({\n  // ... other config ...\n  enableSystemExec: parseBoolean(parsed.ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC),\n  allowedCommandPrefixes: parseCsvList(parsed.ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES),\n  systemExecTimeoutMs: parsed.SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS,\n  // F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n  userPermissions: parseUserPermissions(parsed.USER_PERMISSIONS),\n  allowAdminSkipConfirm: parseBoolean(parsed.ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM),\n  auditLogDir: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_DIR,\n  auditLogMaxSizeMb: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB,\n  auditLogMaxFiles: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES,\n  // ...\n});\n```\n\n### src/services/system-exec-service.js\n```javascript\nimport { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\nimport { assertAllowedCommand, assertSystemExecEnabled } from '../security/system-guard.js';\n\nexport async function executeSystemCommand(command) {\n  assertSystemExecEnabled();\n  const safeCommand = assertAllowedCommand(command);\n\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const child = spawn(safeCommand, {\n      shell: true,\n      stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n    });\n\n    let stdout = '';\n    let stderr = '';\n\n    const timeout = setTimeout(() => {\n      child.kill('SIGTERM');\n      reject(new Error(`系统命令执行超时（>${config.systemExecTimeoutMs}ms）`));\n    }, config.systemExecTimeoutMs);\n\n    child.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => { stdout += chunk.toString(); });\n    child.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => { stderr += chunk.toString(); });\n\n    child.on('error', (error) => {\n      clearTimeout(timeout);\n      reject(new Error(`系统命令执行失败: ${error.message}`));\n    });\n\n    child.on('close', (code) => {\n      clearTimeout(timeout);\n      resolve({ stdout: stdout.trim(), stderr: stderr.trim(), exitCode: code ?? -1 });\n    });\n  });\n}\n```\n\n### src/security/system-guard.js\n```javascript\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\n\nexport function assertSystemExecEnabled() {\n  if (!config.enableSystemExec) {\n    throw new Error('系统命令执行未启用。请在 .env 中设置 ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true。');\n  }\n}\n\nexport function assertAllowedCommand(command) {\n  const normalized = String(command ?? '').trim();\n  if (!normalized) throw new Error('command 不能为空。');\n  if (normalized.length > 2000) throw new Error('command 过长。');\n  if (config.allowedCommandPrefixes.length === 0) {\n    throw new Error('未配置 ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES，已拒绝执行。');\n  }\n  const allowed = config.allowedCommandPrefixes.some((prefix) => normalized.startsWith(prefix));\n  if (!allowed) {\n    throw new Error(`命令不在白名单前缀内。允许前缀: ${config.allowedCommandPrefixes.join(', ')}`);\n  }\n  return normalized;\n}\n```\n\n### src/security/permission-guard.js\n```javascript\nexport const ROLE_HIERARCHY = { viewer: 0, operator: 1, admin: 2 };\n\nconst COMMAND_MIN_ROLE = {\n  status: 'viewer', logs: 'viewer', commits: 'viewer',\n  pipeline: 'operator', bugfix: 'operator', planner: 'operator', retry: 'operator', commit: 'operator',\n  stop: 'admin', reset: 'admin', 'force-unlock': 'admin', exec: 'admin',\n  'commit-amend': 'admin', 'commit-force': 'admin'\n};\n\nconst HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS = new Set(['stop', 'reset', 'force-unlock', 'commit-amend', 'commit-force']);\n\nexport function getUserRole(userId) { /* ... */ }\nexport function isAdmin(userId) { /* ... */ }\nexport function checkCommandPermission(userId, command) { /* ... */ }\n```\n\n### src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n```javascript\nconst DANGEROUS_PATTERNS = [\n  { pattern: /\\.\\./, name: 'path traversal (..)' },\n  { pattern: /[`$]/, name: 'shell injection ($ or `)' },\n  { pattern: /~/, name: 'home directory (~)' },\n  { pattern: /\\$\\(/, name: 'command substitution ($())' },\n  { pattern: /\\|\\|/, name: 'command chain (||)' },\n  { pattern: /&&/, name: 'command chain (&&)' },\n  { pattern: /;/, name: 'command separator (;)' },\n  { pattern: /\\|/, name: 'pipe (|)' },\n  { pattern: /&/, name: 'ampersand (&)' },\n  { pattern: /--exec\\b/, name: 'exec flag (--exec)' },\n  { pattern: /--eval\\b/, name: 'eval flag (--eval)' },\n  // ... more patterns\n];\n\nexport function detectDangerousPatterns(input) { /* ... */ }\nexport function sanitizeParam(input, options = {}) { /* ... */ }\nexport function validatePath(inputPath, allowedRoots) { /* ... */ }\n```\n\n### src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n```javascript\nconst DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS = 60000;\nconst pendingConfirmations = new Map();\n\nexport function createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs = DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS) { /* ... */ }\nexport function checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId) { /* ... */ }\nexport function confirmAction(confirmId, userId) { /* ... */ }\nexport function cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId) { /* ... */ }\n```\n\n### src/services/session-store.js\n```javascript\nclass SessionStore {\n  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n\n  get(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  append(sessionKey, role, content) { /* ... */ }\n  clear(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  toPrompt(sessionKey, channel) { /* ... */ }\n  addCommit(sessionKey, commitInfo) { /* ... */ }\n  getCommits(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  getLastCommit(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n}\n\nexport const sessionStore = new SessionStore();\n```\n\n### src/bot/telegram.js (exec command handler)\n```javascript\nbot.command('exec', async (ctx) => {\n  try {\n    ensureAllowed(ctx);\n    const payload = ctx.message.text.replace('/exec', '').trim();\n    if (!payload) {\n      await ctx.reply('请提供命令，例如 /exec pwd');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    await ctx.reply('正在执行命令。');\n    const result = await executeSystemCommand(payload);\n    const output = [\n      `exitCode: ${result.exitCode}`,\n      result.stdout ? `stdout:\\n${result.stdout}` : 'stdout: (empty)',\n      result.stderr ? `stderr:\\n${result.stderr}` : 'stderr: (empty)'\n    ].join('\\n\\n');\n\n    await replyLargeText(ctx, output);\n  } catch (error) {\n    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n    logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to exec command in telegram');\n    await ctx.reply(`执行失败：${message}`);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 5 - Existing Tests\n\n### tests/security/permission-guard.test.js (excerpts)\n```javascript\ntest('getUserRole returns operator as default for unknown users (AC-1.3)', () => {\n  resetConfig();\n  setConfigForTesting(createTestConfig());\n  assert.equal(getUserRole('unknown-user'), 'operator');\n});\n\ntest('checkCommandPermission denies exec when ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC is false', () => {\n  const config = createTestConfig({ enableSystemExec: false });\n  config.userPermissions.set('admin-user', 'admin');\n  setConfigForTesting(config);\n  const result = checkCommandPermission('admin-user', 'exec');\n  assert.equal(result.allowed, false);\n  assert.ok(result.reason.includes('系统命令执行未启用'));\n});\n\ntest('checkCommandPermission allows admin for exec when ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC is true', () => {\n  const config = createTestConfig({ enableSystemExec: true });\n  config.userPermissions.set('admin-user', 'admin');\n  setConfigForTesting(config);\n  const result = checkCommandPermission('admin-user', 'exec');\n  assert.equal(result.allowed, true);\n});\n```\n\n### tests/security/param-sanitizer.test.js (test patterns reference)\n- Tests for path traversal detection\n- Tests for shell injection detection\n- Tests for command chain detection\n- Tests for safe parameter handling\n- Tests for targetId validation\n\n### tests/security/confirmation-manager.test.js (test patterns reference)\n- Tests for confirmation creation with timeout\n- Tests for confirmation confirmation flow\n- Tests for expired confirmation handling\n- Tests for userId verification\n\n---\n\n## Section 6 - Design Notes for F-009\n\n### Key Design Decisions Needed\n\n1. **Direct Text Mode vs /exec Prefix**\n   - When ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true, plain text messages should be treated as shell commands\n   - Need to distinguish between \"chat with AI\" vs \"execute command\" modes\n   - Option: Use a prefix marker or dedicated mode toggle\n\n2. **Session Working Directory**\n   - Store cwd per session in session-store.js\n   - Default to project root or process.cwd()\n   - /cd command updates session's cwd\n\n3. **Long Output Pagination**\n   - Telegram max message: 4096 chars\n   - Store paginated output in session state\n   - /more command retrieves next chunk\n\n4. **High-Risk Command Detection**\n   - Keywords: rm -rf, sudo, kill, chmod -R, chown, dd, mkfs, etc.\n   - Use confirmation-manager for flow\n   - Blacklist in addition to whitelist\n\n5. **Graceful Timeout Handling**\n   - SIGTERM first, wait for graceful shutdown\n   - SIGKILL after additional grace period\n   - User notification of timeout and termination status\n\n### Files to Create/Modify\n\n**New Files:**\n- `src/services/command-executor-service.js` - Enhanced command execution with cwd, pagination\n- `src/services/output-pager-service.js` - Long output pagination storage\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js` - /cd command handler\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js` - /more command handler\n- `tests/services/command-executor-service.test.js`\n- `tests/services/output-pager-service.test.js`\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js`\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/more.test.js`\n\n**Modified Files:**\n- `src/config.js` - Add COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS config\n- `src/services/session-store.js` - Add cwd tracking per session\n- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Text handler for direct command mode\n- `src/security/permission-guard.js` - Add 'cd', 'more' command permissions\n- `src/security/system-guard.js` - Add blacklist check, high-risk detection\n- `src/services/system-exec-service.js` - Enhanced timeout with SIGTERM→SIGKILL\n\n---\n\n## Section 7 - Implementation Log\n\n(To be filled by Dev agent)\n\n---\n\n## Section 8 - Review Notes\n\n(To be filled by Reviewer agent)\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/009-general-command-executor/context-snapshot.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":64848,"output_tokens":4689,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:15:32.982Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
