{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130215360a3d11e3ec3a4f56","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"id":"202603130215360a3d11e3ec3a4f56","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both are missing. I need to write plan.md and tasks.md myself. Let me create them:"}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:16:11.848Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
{"type":"file-history-snapshot","id":"325b734a-8c9b-4216-87f0-95ab349134a7","timestamp":1773339371851,"isSnapshotUpdate":true,"snapshot":{"messageId":"ce779455-295e-43e0-8ec5-495fbaf0c7b1","trackedFileBackups":{".prizmkit/specs/009-general-command-executor/context-snapshot.md":{"version":1,"backupTime":1773339332973},".prizmkit/specs/009-general-command-executor/plan.md":{"version":1,"backupTime":1773339371851}}},"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:16:11.852Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130215360a3d11e3ec3a4f56","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"id":"202603130215360a3d11e3ec3a4f56","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce342eb6a72b457a92efe7892749d","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Implementation Plan - F-009: General Command Executor\n\n## Overview\n\nTransform PrizmClaw from a pipeline control tool into a general-purpose remote CLI assistant. Users can execute arbitrary shell commands from Telegram and receive stdout/stderr responses.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Telegram Bot                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐│\n│  │ /exec    │  │ /cd      │  │ /more    │  │ Text Handler     ││\n│  │ handler  │  │ handler  │  │ handler  │  │ (direct mode)    ││\n│  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └────────┬─────────┘│\n└───────┼─────────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────┼──────────┘\n        │             │             │                 │\n        ▼             ▼             ▼                 ▼\n┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Command Executor Service                     │\n│  ┌───────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐ │\n│  │ Execute       │  │ Risk Check   │  │ Output Pagination   │ │\n│  │ Command       │──│ (blacklist)  │  │ (4096 char chunks)  │ │\n│  └───────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘ │\n└────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n                             │\n        ┌────────────────────┼────────────────────┐\n        ▼                    ▼                    ▼\n┌───────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────┐\n│ Session Store │  │ Confirmation    │  │ Audit Log Service     │\n│ (cwd per sess)│  │ Manager         │  │ (all exec logged)     │\n└───────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └───────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Data Flow\n\n1. **Command Input**: User sends command via `/exec <cmd>` or direct text (when ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true)\n2. **Authorization**: Permission check → admin role required for exec\n3. **Risk Assessment**: Check blacklist → high-risk keywords → confirmation flow if needed\n4. **Execution**: Spawn process with session's cwd, timeout monitoring\n5. **Output Handling**: Capture stdout/stderr → paginate if >4000 chars → store in session\n6. **Response**: Send to Telegram, support `/more` for remaining pages\n\n### Session State Extensions\n\n```javascript\n// SessionStore extensions\n{\n  messagesBySessionKey: Map,    // existing\n  commitsBySessionKey: Map,    // existing\n  cwdBySessionKey: Map,        // NEW: session -> working directory\n  outputPagesBySessionKey: Map // NEW: session -> paginated output buffer\n}\n```\n\n## Files to Create\n\n### 1. src/services/command-executor-service.js\n**Purpose**: Enhanced command execution with session cwd, timeout with SIGTERM→SIGKILL, risk detection\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `executeCommand({ command, sessionId, userId })` - Main entry point\n- `checkBlacklist(command)` - Reject blacklisted commands\n- `detectHighRiskKeywords(command)` - Detect rm -rf, sudo, etc.\n- `executeWithTimeout(command, cwd, timeoutMs)` - Spawn with timeout\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- session-store (get cwd)\n- confirmation-manager (high-risk confirmation)\n- audit-log-service (log execution)\n- config (blacklist, high-risk keywords, timeout)\n\n### 2. src/services/output-pager-service.js\n**Purpose**: Paginate long output for Telegram's 4096 char limit\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `paginateOutput(text, chunkSize)` - Split into chunks\n- `storeOutputPages(sessionId, pages)` - Store in session\n- `getNextPage(sessionId)` - Get next chunk for /more\n- `clearPages(sessionId)` - Clear after consumption\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- session-store\n\n### 3. src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n**Purpose**: /cd command to change working directory\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `handleCd(handlerContext)` - Change session cwd\n- Validates directory exists\n- Updates session-store.cwdBySessionKey\n\n### 4. src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js\n**Purpose**: /more command to view paginated output\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `handleMore(handlerContext)` - Get next output page\n- Shows \"No more output\" when exhausted\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n### 1. src/config.js\n**Add**:\n- `COMMAND_BLACKLIST: z.string().optional().default('')` - CSV of blocked commands\n- `HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS: z.string().optional().default('rm -rf,sudo,kill,chmod -R,chown,dd,mkfs,shutdown,reboot,halt')`\n- `DIRECT_EXEC_MODE: z.string().optional().default('false')` - Enable direct text execution\n- Parse functions for new config\n\n### 2. src/services/session-store.js\n**Add**:\n- `#cwdBySessionKey = new Map()`\n- `#outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map()`\n- `getCwd(sessionKey)` - Get current working directory\n- `setCwd(sessionKey, cwd)` - Set working directory\n- `getOutputPages(sessionKey)` - Get paginated output\n- `setOutputPages(sessionKey, pages)` - Store paginated output\n- `clearOutputPages(sessionKey)` - Clear output pages\n- Extend `clear()` to reset cwd and output pages\n\n### 3. src/bot/telegram.js\n**Modify**:\n- Import new handlers (cd, more)\n- Register /cd and /more commands\n- Text handler: Check DIRECT_EXEC_MODE, route to exec handler if enabled\n- Update /exec handler to use command-executor-service\n\n### 4. src/security/permission-guard.js\n**Add**:\n- `'cd': 'operator'` - Allow operators to change directory\n- `'more': 'viewer'` - Allow viewers to view paginated output\n- Remove 'exec' from HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS (handled separately with keywords)\n\n### 5. src/security/system-guard.js\n**Add**:\n- `checkCommandBlacklist(command, blacklist)` - Check against blacklist\n- `detectHighRiskKeywords(command, keywords)` - Detect high-risk patterns\n- Export for use in command-executor-service\n\n### 6. src/services/system-exec-service.js\n**Modify**:\n- Add SIGKILL after SIGTERM timeout\n- Return timeout status in result\n- Add cwd parameter support\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **command-executor-service.test.js**\n   - Test blacklist rejection\n   - Test high-risk keyword detection\n   - Test confirmation flow integration\n   - Test cwd handling\n   - Test timeout with SIGTERM→SIGKILL\n\n2. **output-pager-service.test.js**\n   - Test pagination at 4000 char boundary\n   - Test /more navigation\n   - Test page exhaustion\n\n3. **cd.test.js**\n   - Test directory validation\n   - Test session cwd persistence\n   - Test invalid directory handling\n\n4. **more.test.js**\n   - Test no output scenario\n   - Test pagination flow\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **f009-command-executor.integration.test.js**\n   - End-to-end command execution\n   - High-risk confirmation flow\n   - Timeout handling\n   - Blacklist enforcement\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Mapping\n\n| AC# | Requirement | Implementation |\n|-----|-------------|----------------|\n| 1 | Execute shell command, return stdout/stderr | command-executor-service.js |\n| 2 | Configurable whitelist/blacklist | config.js + system-guard.js |\n| 3 | Timeout protection with process termination | system-exec-service.js (SIGTERM→SIGKILL) |\n| 4 | Long output pagination with /more | output-pager-service.js + more.js |\n| 5 | /cd for working directory, session persistence | cd.js + session-store.js |\n| 6 | High-risk command confirmation | confirmation-manager.js + system-guard.js |\n\n## Risk Mitigation\n\n1. **Command Injection**: Keep existing param-sanitizer, add blacklist\n2. **Resource Exhaustion**: Timeout enforced, process killed\n3. **Data Loss**: High-risk commands require confirmation\n4. **Session Isolation**: Cwd is per-session, not global\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- **F-001**: Project infrastructure (✅)\n- **F-006**: Permission system (✅)\n  - Uses permission-guard for role checks\n  - Uses confirmation-manager for high-risk flow\n  - Uses audit-log-service for logging\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/009-general-command-executor/plan.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":69745,"output_tokens":2018,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:16:11.857Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
