d\n  86→\n  87→## Phase 5: Testing & Documentation\n  88→\n  89→- [ ] **T-5.1**: Create integration test\n  90→  - Create tests/integration/f009-command-executor.integration.test.js\n  91→  - Test end-to-end command execution flow\n  92→  - Test high-risk confirmation flow\n  93→  - Test timeout handling\n  94→  - Test blacklist enforcement\n  95→  - Test /cd and /more commands\n  96→\n  97→- [ ] **T-5.2**: Update .prizm-docs\n  98→  - Update runtime/services.prizm with new services\n  99→  - Update runtime/security.prizm with new security functions\n 100→  - Update runtime/bot.prizm with new commands\n 101→  - Add DECISIONS entry for F-009\n 102→\n 103→- [ ] **T-5.3**: Update .env.example\n 104→  - Add COMMAND_BLACKLIST with example value\n 105→  - Add HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS with default value\n 106→  - Add DIRECT_EXEC_MODE with description\n 107→\n 108→## Execution Order\n 109→\n 110→1. T-1.1 (config) → T-1.2 (session-store)\n 111→2. T-2.1 (system-guard) → T-2.2 (permission-guard)\n 112→3. T-3.1 (output-pager) → T-3.2 (command-executor) → T-3.3 (system-exec)\n 113→4. T-4.1 (cd) → T-4.2 (more) → T-4.3 (exec) → T-4.4 (direct mode) → T-4.5 (register)\n 114→5. T-5.1 (integration test) → T-5.2 (prizm docs) → T-5.3 (env example)\n 115→\n 116→## Acceptance Criteria Coverage\n 117→\n 118→| AC | Tasks |\n 119→|----|-------|\n 120→| AC-1: Execute and return stdout/stderr | T-3.2, T-4.3 |\n 121→| AC-2: Whitelist/blacklist security | T-1.1, T-2.1, T-3.2 |\n 122→| AC-3: Timeout with process termination | T-3.3 |\n 123→| AC-4: Long output pagination | T-3.1, T-4.2 |\n 124→| AC-5: /cd for working directory | T-1.2, T-4.1 |\n 125→| AC-6: High-risk command confirmation | T-2.1, T-3.2 |\n 126→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce34f1a139b27766a463bd810f87d","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:29:06.956Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"3dddf65e-ca6e-449f-bea1-b3a5f983a6d9","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce34f39bf03b62f6905ae5fe6d404","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Implementation Plan - F-009: General Command Executor\n   2→\n   3→## Overview\n   4→\n   5→Transform PrizmClaw from a pipeline control tool into a general-purpose remote CLI assistant. Users can execute arbitrary shell commands from Telegram and receive stdout/stderr responses.\n   6→\n   7→## Architecture\n   8→\n   9→### Component Diagram\n  10→\n  11→```\n  12→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  13→│                        Telegram Bot                              │\n  14→│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐│\n  15→│  │ /exec    │  │ /cd      │  │ /more    │  │ Text Handler     ││\n  16→│  │ handler  │  │ handler  │  │ handler  │  │ (direct mode)    ││\n  17→│  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └────────┬─────────┘│\n  18→└───────┼─────────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────┼──────────┘\n  19→        │             │             │                 │\n  20→        ▼             ▼             ▼                 ▼\n  21→┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  22→│                    Command Executor Service                     │\n  23→│  ┌───────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐ │\n  24→│  │ Execute       │  │ Risk Check   │  │ Output Pagination   │ │\n  25→│  │ Command       │──│ (blacklist)  │  │ (4096 char chunks)  │ │\n  26→│  └───────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘ │\n  27→└────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n  28→                             │\n  29→        ┌────────────────────┼────────────────────┐\n  30→        ▼                    ▼                    ▼\n  31→┌───────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────┐\n  32→│ Session Store │  │ Confirmation    │  │ Audit Log Service     │\n  33→│ (cwd per sess)│  │ Manager         │  │ (all exec logged)     │\n  34→└───────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └───────────────────────┘\n  35→```\n  36→\n  37→### Data Flow\n  38→\n  39→1. **Command Input**: User sends command via `/exec <cmd>` or direct text (when ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true)\n  40→2. **Authorization**: Permission check → admin role required for exec\n  41→3. **Risk Assessment**: Check blacklist → high-risk keywords → confirmation flow if needed\n  42→4. **Execution**: Spawn process with session's cwd, timeout monitoring\n  43→5. **Output Handling**: Capture stdout/stderr → paginate if >4000 chars → store in session\n  44→6. **Response**: Send to Telegram, support `/more` for remaining pages\n  45→\n  46→### Session State Extensions\n  47→\n  48→```javascript\n  49→// SessionStore extensions\n  50→{\n  51→  messagesBySessionKey: Map,    // existing\n  52→  commitsBySessionKey: Map,    // existing\n  53→  cwdBySessionKey: Map,        // NEW: session -> working directory\n  54→  outputPagesBySessionKey: Map // NEW: session -> paginated output buffer\n  55→}\n  56→```\n  57→\n  58→## Files to Create\n  59→\n  60→### 1. src/services/command-executor-service.js\n  61→**Purpose**: Enhanced command execution with session cwd, timeout with SIGTERM→SIGKILL, risk detection\n  62→\n  63→**Key Functions**:\n  64→- `executeCommand({ command, sessionId, userId })` - Main entry point\n  65→- `checkBlacklist(command)` - Reject blacklisted commands\n  66→- `detectHighRiskKeywords(command)` - Detect rm -rf, sudo, etc.\n  67→- `executeWithTimeout(command, cwd, timeoutMs)` - Spawn with timeout\n  68→\n  69→**Dependencies**:\n  70→- session-store (get cwd)\n  71→- confirmation-manager (high-risk confirmation)\n  72→- audit-log-service (log execution)\n  73→- config (blacklist, high-risk keywords, timeout)\n  74→\n  75→### 2. src/services/output-pager-service.js\n  76→**Purpose**: Paginate long output for Telegram's 4096 char limit\n  77→\n  78→**Key Functions**:\n  79→- `paginateOutput(text, chunkSize)` - Split into chunks\n  80→- `storeOutputPages(sessionId, pages)` - Store in session\n  81→- `getNextPage(sessionId)` - Get next chunk for /more\n  82→- `clearPages(sessionId)` - Clear after consumption\n  83→\n  84→**Dependencies**:\n  85→- session-store\n  86→\n  87→### 3. src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n  88→**Purpose**: /cd command to change working directory\n  89→\n  90→**Key Functions**:\n  91→- `handleCd(handlerContext)` - Change session cwd\n  92→- Validates directory exists\n  93→- Updates session-store.cwdBySessionKey\n  94→\n  95→### 4. src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js\n  96→**Purpose**: /more command to view paginated output\n  97→\n  98→**Key Functions**:\n  99→- `handleMore(handlerContext)` - Get next output page\n 100→- Shows \"No more output\" when exhausted\n 101→\n 102→## Files to Modify\n 103→\n 104→### 1. src/config.js\n 105→**Add**:\n 106→- `COMMAND_BLACKLIST: z.string().optional().default('')` - CSV of blocked commands\n 107→- `HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS: z.string().optional().default('rm -rf,sudo,kill,chmod -R,chown,dd,mkfs,shutdown,reboot,halt')`\n 108→- `DIRECT_EXEC_MODE: z.string().optional().default('false')` - Enable direct text execution\n 109→- Parse functions for new config\n 110→\n 111→### 2. src/services/session-store.js\n 112→**Add**:\n 113→- `#cwdBySessionKey = new Map()`\n 114→- `#outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map()`\n 115→- `getCwd(sessionKey)` - Get current working directory\n 116→- `setCwd(sessionKey, cwd)` - Set working directory\n 117→- `getOutputPages(sessionKey)` - Get paginated output\n 118→- `setOutputPages(sessionKey, pages)` - Store paginated output\n 119→- `clearOutputPages(sessionKey)` - Clear output pages\n 120→- Extend `clear()` to reset cwd and output pages\n 121→\n 122→### 3. src/bot/telegram.js\n 123→**Modify**:\n 124→- Import new handlers (cd, more)\n 125→- Register /cd and /more commands\n 126→- Text handler: Check DIRECT_EXEC_MODE, route to exec handler if enabled\n 127→- Update /exec handler to use command-executor-service\n 128→\n 129→### 4. src/security/permission-guard.js\n 130→**Add**:\n 131→- `'cd': 'operator'` - Allow operators to change directory\n 132→- `'more': 'viewer'` - Allow viewers to view paginated output\n 133→- Remove 'exec' from HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS (handled separately with keywords)\n 134→\n 135→### 5. src/security/system-guard.js\n 136→**Add**:\n 137→- `checkCommandBlacklist(command, blacklist)` - Check against blacklist\n 138→- `detectHighRiskKeywords(command, keywords)` - Detect high-risk patterns\n 139→- Export for use in command-executor-service\n 140→\n 141→### 6. src/services/system-exec-service.js\n 142→**Modify**:\n 143→- Add SIGKILL after SIGTERM timeout\n 144→- Return timeout status in result\n 145→- Add cwd parameter support\n 146→\n 147→## Testing Strategy\n 148→\n 149→### Unit Tests\n 150→\n 151→1. **command-executor-service.test.js**\n 152→   - Test blacklist rejection\n 153→   - Test high-risk keyword detection\n 154→   - Test confirmation flow integration\n 155→   - Test cwd handling\n 156→   - Test timeout with SIGTERM→SIGKILL\n 157→\n 158→2. **output-pager-service.test.js**\n 159→   - Test pagination at 4000 char boundary\n 160→   - Test /more navigation\n 161→   - Test page exhaustion\n 162→\n 163→3. **cd.test.js**\n 164→   - Test directory validation\n 165→   - Test session cwd persistence\n 166→   - Test invalid directory handling\n 167→\n 168→4. **more.test.js**\n 169→   - Test no output scenario\n 170→   - Test pagination flow\n 171→\n 172→### Integration Tests\n 173→\n 174→1. **f009-command-executor.integration.test.js**\n 175→   - End-to-end command execution\n 176→   - High-risk confirmation flow\n 177→   - Timeout handling\n 178→   - Blacklist enforcement\n 179→\n 180→## Acceptance Criteria Mapping\n 181→\n 182→| AC# | Requirement | Implementation |\n 183→|-----|-------------|----------------|\n 184→| 1 | Execute shell command, return stdout/stderr | command-executor-service.js |\n 185→| 2 | Configurable whitelist/blacklist | config.js + system-guard.js |\n 186→| 3 | Timeout protection with process termination | system-exec-service.js (SIGTERM→SIGKILL) |\n 187→| 4 | Long output pagination with /more | output-pager-service.js + more.js |\n 188→| 5 | /cd for working directory, session persistence | cd.js + session-store.js |\n 189→| 6 | High-risk command confirmation | confirmation-manager.js + system-guard.js |\n 190→\n 191→## Risk Mitigation\n 192→\n 193→1. **Command Injection**: Keep existing param-sanitizer, add blacklist\n 194→2. **Resource Exhaustion**: Timeout enforced, process killed\n 195→3. **Data Loss**: High-risk commands require confirmation\n 196→4. **Session Isolation**: Cwd is per-session, not global\n 197→\n 198→## Dependencies\n 199→\n 200→- **F-001**: Project infrastructure (✅)\n 201→- **F-006**: Permission system (✅)\n 202→  - Uses permission-guard for role checks\n 203→  - Uses confirmation-manager for high-risk flow\n 204→  - Uses audit-log-service for logging\n 205→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce34f1a139b27766a463bd810f87d","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:29:06.957Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
