{"type":"user","uuid":"f04ad3e3-7634-4303-a906-9ecd755e218c","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce350c62bf10e685b3339941fd043","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Tasks - F-009: General Command Executor\n   2→\n   3→## Phase 1: Configuration & Infrastructure\n   4→\n   5→- [x] **T-1.1**: Add new config variables to src/config.js\n   6→  - Add COMMAND_BLACKLIST env var parsing\n   7→  - Add HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS env var parsing\n   8→  - Add DIRECT_EXEC_MODE env var parsing\n   9→  - Export commandBlacklist, highRiskKeywords, directExecMode in config object\n  10→\n  11→- [x] **T-1.2**: Extend session-store.js for cwd and output pages\n  12→  - Add #cwdBySessionKey Map\n  13→  - Add #outputPagesBySessionKey Map\n  14→  - Add getCwd(sessionKey) method\n  15→  - Add setCwd(sessionKey, cwd) method\n  16→  - Add getOutputPages(sessionKey) method\n  17→  - Add setOutputPages(sessionKey, pages) method\n  18→  - Add clearOutputPages(sessionKey) method\n  19→  - Update clear() to reset cwd and output pages\n  20→\n  21→## Phase 2: Security Extensions\n  22→\n  23→- [x] **T-2.1**: Extend system-guard.js with blacklist and high-risk detection\n  24→  - Add checkCommandBlacklist(command, blacklist) function\n  25→  - Add detectHighRiskKeywords(command, keywords) function\n  26→  - Export new functions for use in command-executor-service\n  27→\n  28→- [x] **T-2.2**: Update permission-guard.js for new commands\n  29→  - Add 'cd': 'operator' to COMMAND_MIN_ROLE\n  30→  - Add 'more': 'viewer' to COMMAND_MIN_ROLE\n  31→  - Remove 'exec' from HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS (handled via keywords)\n  32→\n  33→## Phase 3: Core Services\n  34→\n  35→- [x] **T-3.1**: Create output-pager-service.js\n  36→  - Implement paginateOutput(text, chunkSize = 4000)\n  37→  - Implement storeOutputPages(sessionId, pages)\n  38→  - Implement getNextPage(sessionId)\n  39→  - Implement clearPages(sessionId)\n  40→  - Write unit tests in tests/services/output-pager-service.test.js\n  41→\n  42→- [x] **T-3.2**: Create command-executor-service.js\n  43→  - Implement executeCommand({ command, sessionId, userId })\n  44→  - Integrate blacklist check\n  45→  - Integrate high-risk keyword detection\n  46→  - Integrate confirmation flow for high-risk commands\n  47→  - Integrate session cwd\n  48→  - Use output-pager-service for long output\n  49→  - Log to audit-log-service\n  50→  - Write unit tests in tests/services/command-executor-service.test.js\n  51→\n  52→- [x] **T-3.3**: Enhance system-exec-service.js timeout handling\n  53→  - Add SIGKILL after SIGTERM timeout (grace period: 5s)\n  54→  - Return timeout status in result object\n  55→  - Add cwd parameter support\n  56→  - Update tests\n  57→\n  58→## Phase 4: Command Handlers\n  59→\n  60→- [x] **T-4.1**: Create /cd command handler (src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js)\n  61→  - Implement handleCd function\n  62→  - Validate directory exists and is accessible\n  63→  - Update session cwd via session-store\n  64→  - Write unit tests in tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js\n  65→\n  66→- [x] **T-4.2**: Create /more command handler (src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js)\n  67→  - Implement handleMore function\n  68→  - Fetch next page from output-pager-service\n  69→  - Handle \"no more output\" scenario\n  70→  - Write unit tests in tests/bot/commands/handlers/more.test.js\n  71→\n  72→- [x] **T-4.3**: Update /exec handler in telegram.js\n  73→  - Import command-executor-service\n  74→  - Replace executeSystemCommand with executeCommand\n  75→  - Handle paginated output\n  76→\n  77→- [x] **T-4.4**: Add direct text mode to telegram.js\n  78→  - Check DIRECT_EXEC_MODE config\n  79→  - Route non-command text to exec handler when enabled\n  80→  - Keep chat mode as default when disabled\n  81→\n  82→- [x] **T-4.5**: Register new commands in telegram.js\n  83→  - Import cd and more handlers\n  84→  - Register /cd command\n  85→  - Register /more command\n  86→\n  87→## Phase 5: Testing & Documentation\n  88→\n  89→- [x] **T-5.1**: Create integration test\n  90→  - Create tests/integration/f009-command-executor.integration.test.js\n  91→  - Test end-to-end command execution flow\n  92→  - Test high-risk confirmation flow\n  93→  - Test timeout handling\n  94→  - Test blacklist enforcement\n  95→  - Test /cd and /more commands\n  96→\n  97→- [x] **T-5.2**: Update .prizm-docs\n  98→  - Update runtime/services.prizm with new services\n  99→  - Update runtime/security.prizm with new security functions\n 100→  - Update runtime/bot.prizm with new commands\n 101→  - Add DECISIONS entry for F-009\n 102→\n 103→- [x] **T-5.3**: Update .env.example\n 104→  - Add COMMAND_BLACKLIST with example value\n 105→  - Add HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS with default value\n 106→  - Add DIRECT_EXEC_MODE with description\n 107→\n 108→## Execution Order\n 109→\n 110→1. T-1.1 (config) → T-1.2 (session-store)\n 111→2. T-2.1 (system-guard) → T-2.2 (permission-guard)\n 112→3. T-3.1 (output-pager) → T-3.2 (command-executor) → T-3.3 (system-exec)\n 113→4. T-4.1 (cd) → T-4.2 (more) → T-4.3 (exec) → T-4.4 (direct mode) → T-4.5 (register)\n 114→5. T-5.1 (integration test) → T-5.2 (prizm docs) → T-5.3 (env example)\n 115→\n 116→## Acceptance Criteria Coverage\n 117→\n 118→| AC | Tasks |\n 119→|----|-------|\n 120→| AC-1: Execute and return stdout/stderr | T-3.2, T-4.3 |\n 121→| AC-2: Whitelist/blacklist security | T-1.1, T-2.1, T-3.2 |\n 122→| AC-3: Timeout with process termination | T-3.3 |\n 123→| AC-4: Long output pagination | T-3.1, T-4.2 |\n 124→| AC-5: /cd for working directory | T-1.2, T-4.1 |\n 125→| AC-6: High-risk command confirmation | T-2.1, T-3.2 |\n 126→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce34f1a139b27766a463bd810f87d","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:30:48.239Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
