{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313023315691a5afd4aba4c90","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"id":"20260313023315691a5afd4aba4c90","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce3531bf6bb9d5d1d601c8ddfeb92","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/009-general-command-executor/context-snapshot.md","new_string":"## Section 7 - Implementation Log\n\n### Files Created\n- `src/services/command-executor-service.js` - Main command execution service with blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, session cwd, output pagination, and audit logging\n- `src/services/output-pager-service.js` - Output pagination service for Telegram 4096 char limit\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js` - /cd command handler for session working directory\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js` - /more command handler for paginated output\n- `tests/services/command-executor-service.test.js` - Unit tests for command executor\n- `tests/services/output-pager-service.test.js` - Unit tests for output pager\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js` - Unit tests for /cd handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/more.test.js` - Unit tests for /more handler\n- `tests/integration/f009-command-executor.integration.test.js` - Integration tests covering AC-1 through AC-6\n\n### Files Modified\n- `src/config.js` - Added COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE config variables\n- `src/services/session-store.js` - Added #cwdBySessionKey, #outputPagesBySessionKey Maps and corresponding getter/setter methods\n- `src/services/system-exec-service.js` - Enhanced timeout handling with SIGTERM→SIGKILL, added cwd parameter support, added timedOut flag in result\n- `src/security/system-guard.js` - Added checkCommandBlacklist() and detectHighRiskKeywords() functions\n- `src/security/permission-guard.js` - Added 'cd': 'operator' and 'more': 'viewer' to COMMAND_MIN_ROLE\n- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Updated /exec handler to use command-executor-service, added /cd and /more command registration, added direct text mode support\n- `.env.example` - Added COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE with descriptions\n- `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` - Added F-009 DECISIONS entry\n- `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` - Added command-executor-service and output-pager-service to KEY_FILES and PUBLIC_APIS, added F-009 DECISIONS entry\n- `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm` - Added checkCommandBlacklist and detectHighRiskKeywords to INTERFACES, updated COMMAND_PERMISSIONS, added F-009 DECISIONS entry\n- `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm` - Added /cd and /more to INTERFACES, added F-009 DECISIONS entry\n\n### Key Implementation Decisions\n1. **Blacklist vs Whitelist**: Implemented both - whitelist via existing ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES, blacklist via new COMMAND_BLACKLIST. Blacklist check happens first, then whitelist.\n2. **High-risk Keywords**: Used simple substring matching for detection. Keywords like 'sudo', 'rm -rf', 'kill' trigger confirmation flow.\n3. **Timeout Handling**: SIGTERM first, then SIGKILL after 5-second grace period. Result includes timedOut flag.\n4. **Pagination**: 4000 char chunk size (leaving room for Telegram message formatting). Pages stored in session for /more retrieval.\n5. **Session CWD**: Per-session working directory stored in session-store, defaulting to process.cwd().\n\n### Deviations from plan.md\n- No significant deviations. Implementation followed plan.md closely.\n- Integration tests adapted to work with frozen config by testing functions directly where needed.\n\n---\n\n## Section 8 - Review Notes","old_string":"## Section 7 - Implementation Log\n\n(To be filled by Dev agent)\n\n---\n\n## Section 8 - Review Notes"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":70807,"output_tokens":882,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"ser