rc/config.js` - Add COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS config\n 501→- `src/services/session-store.js` - Add cwd tracking per session\n 502→- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Text handler for direct command mode\n 503→- `src/security/permission-guard.js` - Add 'cd', 'more' command permissions\n 504→- `src/security/system-guard.js` - Add blacklist check, high-risk detection\n 505→- `src/services/system-exec-service.js` - Enhanced timeout with SIGTERM→SIGKILL\n 506→\n 507→---\n 508→\n 509→## Section 7 - Implementation Log\n 510→\n 511→### Files Created\n 512→\n 513→| Path | Purpose |\n 514→|------|---------|\n 515→| `src/services/command-executor-service.js` | Main command execution service with blacklist check, high-risk keyword detection, confirmation flow, session cwd, output pagination |\n 516→| `src/services/output-pager-service.js` | Pagination service for long output (4000 char chunks) |\n 517→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js` | /cd command handler for changing working directory |\n 518→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js` | /more command handler for viewing paginated output |\n 519→| `tests/config/f009-config.test.js` | Tests for F-009 config variables |\n 520→| `tests/services/session-store-f009.test.js` | Tests for session store extensions |\n 521→| `tests/security/system-guard-f009.test.js` | Tests for blacklist and high-risk detection |\n 522→| `tests/security/permission-guard-f009.test.js` | Tests for cd/more command permissions |\n 523→| `tests/services/output-pager-service.test.js` | Tests for pagination service |\n 524→| `tests/services/command-executor-service.test.js` | Tests for command executor service |\n 525→| `tests/services/system-exec-service-f009.test.js` | Tests for timeout handling enhancements |\n 526→| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js` | Tests for /cd handler |\n 527→| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/more.test.js` | Tests for /more handler |\n 528→| `tests/integration/f009-command-executor.integration.test.js` | End-to-end integration tests |\n 529→\n 530→### Files Modified\n 531→\n 532→| Path | Changes |\n 533→|------|---------|\n 534→| `src/config.js` | Added COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE config variables |\n 535→| `src/services/session-store.js` | Added #cwdBySessionKey, #outputPagesBySessionKey maps and getCwd, setCwd, getOutputPages, setOutputPages, clearOutputPages methods |\n 536→| `src/security/system-guard.js` | Added checkCommandBlacklist(), detectHighRiskKeywords() functions |\n 537→| `src/security/permission-guard.js` | Added 'cd': 'operator', 'more': 'viewer' to COMMAND_MIN_ROLE |\n 538→| `src/services/system-exec-service.js` | Enhanced with cwd option, SIGTERM→SIGKILL timeout handling, timedOut status in result |\n 539→| `src/bot/telegram.js` | Updated /exec handler to use command-executor-service, added /cd and /more commands, added direct exec mode for text messages |\n 540→| `.env.example` | Added COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE documentation |\n 541→| `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` | Updated KEY_FILES, INTERFACES, TRAPS, and DECISIONS for F-009 |\n 542→| `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` | Added command-executor-service and output-pager-service to KEY_FILES and PUBLIC_APIS |\n 543→| `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm` | Added checkCommandBlacklist and detectHighRiskKeywords to INTERFACES, updated COMMAND_PERMISSIONS |\n 544→| `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm` | Added /cd and /more commands to INTERFACES |\n 545→\n 546→### Key Implementation Decisions\n 547→\n 548→1. **Confirmation Flow**: High-risk commands trigger confirmation via confirmation-manager.js. The executeCommand function returns `needsConfirmation: true` with a `confirmationId` that must be passed to `confirmHighRiskCommand()`.\n 549→\n 550→2. **Pagination Strategy**: Output is paginated at 4000 characters (leaving room for Telegram's 4096 limit). First page is returned immediately, remaining pages stored in session for `/more` retrieval.\n 551→\n 552→3. **Timeout Handling**: Enhanced to use SIGTERM first, then SIGKILL after 5-second grace period. The `timedOut` flag is returned in the result object instead of throwing an error.\n 553→\n 554→4. **Direct Exec Mode**: When `DIRECT_EXEC_MODE=true`, plain text messages that don't look like chat (no CJK characters) are treated as shell commands. Falls back to chat mode on failure.\n 555→\n 556→5. **Permission Model**: \n 557→   - `/cd` requires 'operator' role (can change directory)\n 558→   - `/more` requires 'viewer' role (can view output)\n 559→   - `/exec` requires 'admin' role (existing)\n 560→\n 561→### Deviations from plan.md\n 562→\n 563→- None. Implementation followed the plan.md specification exactly.\n 564→\n 565→### Test Coverage\n 566→\n 567→All 15 tasks completed with passing tests:\n 568→- Unit tests for all new services and handlers\n 569→- Integration tests covering all 6 acceptance criteria\n 570→- 769/780 total tests passing (11 pre-existing failures unrelated to F-009)\n 571→\n 572→---\n 573→\n 574→## Section 8 - Review Notes\n 575→\n 576→(To be filled by Reviewer agent)\n 577→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce354b726b8a4df5dbec4c5680ecb","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:35:15.063Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
