{"type":"user","uuid":"c9e16a7a-e807-4245-8a5f-253a83ec43bb","session_id":"40f278db-8cd3-4168-987a-9ae4d774284e","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3571ee4d47440505058cf17e6b4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command: grep -A 50 \"## Section 7 - Implementation Log\" .prizmkit/specs/009-general-command-executor/context-snapshot.md 2>/dev/null | head -80\nStdout: ## Section 7 - Implementation Log\n\n### Files Created\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/services/command-executor-service.js` | Main command execution service with blacklist check, high-risk keyword detection, confirmation flow, session cwd, output pagination |\n| `src/services/output-pager-service.js` | Pagination service for long output (4000 char chunks) |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js` | /cd command handler for changing working directory |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js` | /more command handler for viewing paginated output |\n| `tests/config/f009-config.test.js` | Tests for F-009 config variables |\n| `tests/services/session-store-f009.test.js` | Tests for session store extensions |\n| `tests/security/system-guard-f009.test.js` | Tests for blacklist and high-risk detection |\n| `tests/security/permission-guard-f009.test.js` | Tests for cd/more command permissions |\n| `tests/services/output-pager-service.test.js` | Tests for pagination service |\n| `tests/services/command-executor-service.test.js` | Tests for command executor service |\n| `tests/services/system-exec-service-f009.test.js` | Tests for timeout handling enhancements |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js` | Tests for /cd handler |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/more.test.js` | Tests for /more handler |\n| `tests/integration/f009-command-executor.integration.test.js` | End-to-end integration tests |\n\n### Files Modified\n\n| Path | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/config.js` | Added COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE config variables |\n| `src/services/session-store.js` | Added #cwdBySessionKey, #outputPagesBySessionKey maps and getCwd, setCwd, getOutputPages, setOutputPages, clearOutputPages methods |\n| `src/security/system-guard.js` | Added checkCommandBlacklist(), detectHighRiskKeywords() functions |\n| `src/security/permission-guard.js` | Added 'cd': 'operator', 'more': 'viewer' to COMMAND_MIN_ROLE |\n| `src/services/system-exec-service.js` | Enhanced with cwd option, SIGTERM→SIGKILL timeout handling, timedOut status in result |\n| `src/bot/telegram.js` | Updated /exec handler to use command-executor-service, added /cd and /more commands, added direct exec mode for text messages |\n| `.env.example` | Added COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE documentation |\n| `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` | Updated KEY_FILES, INTERFACES, TRAPS, and DECISIONS for F-009 |\n| `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` | Added command-executor-service and output-pager-service to KEY_FILES and PUBLIC_APIS |\n| `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm` | Added checkCommandBlacklist and detectHighRiskKeywords to INTERFACES, updated COMMAND_PERMISSIONS |\n| `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm` | Added /cd and /more commands to INTERFACES |\n\n### Key Implementation Decisions\n\n1. **Confirmation Flow**: High-risk commands trigger confirmation via confirmation-manager.js. The executeCommand function returns `needsConfirmation: true` with a `confirmationId` that must be passed to `confirmHighRiskCommand()`.\n\n2. **Pagination Strategy**: Output is paginated at 4000 characters (leaving room for Telegram's 4096 limit). First page is returned immediately, remaining pages stored in session for `/more` retrieval.\n\n3. **Timeout Handling**: Enhanced to use SIGTERM first, then SIGKILL after 5-second grace period. The `timedOut` flag is returned in the result object instead of throwing an error.\n\n4. **Direct Exec Mode**: When `DIRECT_EXEC_MODE=true`, plain text messages that don't look like chat (no CJK characters) are treated as shell commands. Falls back to chat mode on failure.\n\n5. **Permission Model**: \n   - `/cd` requires 'operator' role (can change directory)\n   - `/more` requires 'viewer' role (can view output)\n   - `/exec` requires 'admin' role (existing)\n\nStderr: (empty)\nExit Code: 0\nSignal: (none)"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3571ee4d47440505058cf17e6b4","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:37:44.719Z","_requestId":"28efb2d2223148a8a0cf1e344695caa8"}
