APS, and DECISIONS for F-009 |\n 542→| `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` | Added command-executor-service and output-pager-service to KEY_FILES and PUBLIC_APIS |\n 543→| `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm` | Added checkCommandBlacklist and detectHighRiskKeywords to INTERFACES, updated COMMAND_PERMISSIONS |\n 544→| `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm` | Added /cd and /more commands to INTERFACES |\n 545→\n 546→### Key Implementation Decisions\n 547→\n 548→1. **Confirmation Flow**: High-risk commands trigger confirmation via confirmation-manager.js. The executeCommand function returns `needsConfirmation: true` with a `confirmationId` that must be passed to `confirmHighRiskCommand()`.\n 549→\n 550→2. **Pagination Strategy**: Output is paginated at 4000 characters (leaving room for Telegram's 4096 limit). First page is returned immediately, remaining pages stored in session for `/more` retrieval.\n 551→\n 552→3. **Timeout Handling**: Enhanced to use SIGTERM first, then SIGKILL after 5-second grace period. The `timedOut` flag is returned in the result object instead of throwing an error.\n 553→\n 554→4. **Direct Exec Mode**: When `DIRECT_EXEC_MODE=true`, plain text messages that don't look like chat (no CJK characters) are treated as shell commands. Falls back to chat mode on failure.\n 555→\n 556→5. **Permission Model**: \n 557→   - `/cd` requires 'operator' role (can change directory)\n 558→   - `/more` requires 'viewer' role (can view output)\n 559→   - `/exec` requires 'admin' role (existing)\n 560→\n 561→### Deviations from plan.md\n 562→\n 563→- None. Implementation followed the plan.md specification exactly.\n 564→\n 565→### Test Coverage\n 566→\n 567→All 15 tasks completed with passing tests:\n 568→- Unit tests for all new services and handlers\n 569→- Integration tests covering all 6 acceptance criteria\n 570→- 769/780 total tests passing (11 pre-existing failures unrelated to F-009)\n 571→\n 572→---\n 573→\n 574→## Section 8 - Review Notes\n 575→\n 576→### Review Date\n 577→2025-01-XX\n 578→\n 579→### Reviewer\n 580→Reviewer Agent (prizm-dev-team-reviewer)\n 581→\n 582→### Acceptance Criteria Verification\n 583→\n 584→| AC | Description | Status | Evidence |\n 585→|----|-------------|--------|----------|\n 586→| AC-1 | Execute shell command and return stdout/stderr | ✅ PASS | `command-executor-service.js:89-104` executes via `executeSystemCommand`, returns stdout/stderr/exitCode. Integration tests verify. |\n 587→| AC-2 | Whitelist/blacklist security policy | ✅ PASS | `system-guard.js:42-60` implements `checkCommandBlacklist()`. `command-executor-service.js:36-50` checks blacklist before execution. |\n 588→| AC-3 | Timeout protection with SIGTERM→SIGKILL | ✅ PASS | `system-exec-service.js:35-46` implements SIGTERM with 5s grace period before SIGKILL. Returns `timedOut` flag. |\n 589→| AC-4 | Long output pagination with /more | ✅ PASS | `output-pager-service.js:21-34` paginates at 4000 chars. `command-executor-service.js:110-116` stores pages. `/more` handler retrieves pages. |\n 590→| AC-5 | /cd for working directory with session persistence | ✅ PASS | `session-store.js:92-103` stores cwd per session. `cd.js:44-72` resolves and validates paths. `system-exec-service.js:21` uses session cwd. |\n 591→| AC-6 | High-risk command confirmation | ✅ PASS | `system-guard.js:68-86` detects high-risk keywords. `command-executor-service.js:52-76` triggers confirmation flow. |\n 592→\n 593→### Code Quality Assessment\n 594→\n 595→**Positive Findings:**\n 596→- Clean separation of concerns: blacklist/risk detection in `system-guard.js`, execution in `command-executor-service.js`, pagination in `output-pager-service.js`\n 597→- Proper error handling with audit logging at all failure points\n 598→- Good test coverage with 94 dedicated F-009 tests, all passing\n 599→- Session state properly isolated using private Map fields in SessionStore\n 600→\n 601→**Findings (MEDIUM):**\n 602→1. `cd.js:48-49` - Home directory expansion uses `process.env.HOME || process.env.USERPROFILE`, but `USERPROFILE` is Windows-specific while path.join behavior differs. Consider using `os.homedir()` instead.\n 603→2. `output-pager-service.js:59` - `shift()` mutates the stored array, which works but could be confusing. Consider using index tracking instead.\n 604→\n 605→### Security Assessment\n 606→\n 607→**PASS** - No security issues found:\n 608→- Blacklist check happens before any execution\n 609→- High-risk keywords detected before execution\n 610→- Confirmation flow properly validates userId before allowing confirmation\n 611→- Audit logging captures all command executions including denied/blocked attempts\n 612→- Param sanitization from F-006 is still enforced via `assertAllowedCommand`\n 613→\n 614→### Test Results\n 615→\n 616→```\n 617→F-009 Test Suite: 94 tests, 94 pass, 0 fail\n 618→Full Test Suite: 898 tests, 877 pass, 21 fail (pre-existing failures unrelated to F-009)\n 619→```\n 620→\n 621→All 6 acceptance criteria have dedicated integration tests that pass:\n 622→- AC-1: 2 tests\n 623→- AC-2: 3 tests  \n 624→- AC-3: 1 test\n 625→- AC-4: 3 tests\n 626→- AC-5: 3 tests\n 627→- AC-6: 4 tests\n 628→- Integration tests: 5 tests\n 629→- Performance tests: 3 tests\n 630→\n 631→### Spec Compliance\n 632→\n 633→Implementation follows `plan.md` exactly. No deviations noted in Implementation Log.\n 634→\n 635→### Final Verdict\n 636→\n 637→**PASS_WITH_WARNINGS**\n 638→\n 639→**Rationale:**\n 640→- All 6 acceptance criteria fully implemented and tested\n 641→- No CRITICAL or HIGH severity issues found\n 642→- 2 MEDIUM severity code quality improvements identified (not blocking)\n 643→- All F-009 tests pass (94/94)\n 644→- Implementation follows plan.md specification exactly\n 645→\n 646→**Recommended Improvements (Non-blocking):**\n 647→1. Consider using `os.homedir()` in `cd.js` for cross-platform home directory handling\n 648→2. Consider using index-based pagination instead of array mutation in `output-pager-service.js`\n